COMPONENT NAME: IKM Netezza Incremental Update
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Integration Knowledge Module - Integrates data in a Netezza target table in incremental update mode. - Inexistent rows are inserted; already existing rows are updated. - Data can be controlled. Invalid data is isolated in the Error Table and can be recycled. - When using this module with a journalized source table, it is possible to synchronize deletions. - This module manages statistics and distribution options for the target and integration tables.
Restrictions: - When working with journalized data, if the "Synchronize deletions from journal" is executed, the deleted rows on the target are committed regardless of the COMMIT option - Comparison of data is made using the Update Key defined in the interface. It has to be set. - The TRUNCATE option cannot work if the target table is referenced by another table (foreign key) - The FLOW_CONTROL and STATIC_CONTROL options call the Check Knowledge Module to isolate invalid data (if no CKM is set, an error occurs). Both options must be set to NO in the case when an Integration Interface populates a TEMPORARY target datastore. - The option ANALYZE_TARGET will evaluate correct statictics only if COMMIT is set to Yes. Otherwise, the IKM will gather statistics based upon old data.
Automatically attempts to insert data into the Target Datastore of the Interface
Uncheck this option if you do not want to update existing data in the target table
Check this option to synchronize journalized deletions. This option will take effect only if one source table is journalized in your interface.
Check this option if you wish to perform flow control.
Check this option to recycle data rejected from a previous control.
Check this option to control the target table after having inserted or updated target data.
Check this option if you wish to truncate the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to create the target table.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
Check this option if you wish to generate statistics for the target table at the end of the interface.

Specify distribution column to spread each table across the nodes.
It is important that the chosen column has a high cardinality (many distint values) to ensure evenly spread data to allow maximum processing performance. Pleaes follow Netezza's recommandation on choosing a such a column. Valid options are [PK] Primary key of target table [UK] Update key set in interface [RANDOM] Random distribution <list of cols> This comma separated list of target columns. If no value is set (empty), no index will be created.
Check this option if you wish to generate statistics on the integration table before loading data into the target table.
Remove deleted rows from flow table

	", "", "(((INS OR UPD) AND NOT TRG) AND REW)")%>, IND_UPDATE ) select DISTINCT <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "(((INS OR UPD) AND NOT TRG) AND REW)")%>, 'I' IND_UPDATE from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> E where not exists ( select 'X' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> T where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME] = E.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "UK")%> ) and E.ODI_ORIGIN = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>' and E.ODI_ERR_TYPE = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>'

delete from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> where exists ( select 'X' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> I where <%=odiRef.getColList("", odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A") + ".[COL_NAME] = I.[COL_NAME]", "\n\t\tand \t", "", "UK")%> and IND_UPDATE = 'D' )

update <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "W")%> set IND_UPDATE = 'U' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> AS T where ( <%=odiRef.getColList("","T.[COL_NAME]="+odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "W")+".[COL_NAME]", " and ", "", "UK")%> )

Update <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "W")%> set IND_UPDATE = 'N' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> AS T where ( <%=odiRef.getColList("","T.[COL_NAME]="+odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "W")+".[COL_NAME]", " and ", "", "UK")%> ) and ( <%=odiRef.getColList("","((T.[COL_NAME]="+odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "W")+".[COL_NAME]) Or (T.[COL_NAME] IS NULL and "+odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "W")+".[COL_NAME] IS NULL))", " \nand\t", "", "(UPD AND (NOT TRG)) AND (NOT UK) ")%> )

Update <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> set <%=odiRef.getColList("","[COL_NAME]=S.[COL_NAME]", " , " , "", "UPD AND (NOT TRG) AND (NOT UK)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(odiRef.getColList(","," ", "" , "", "(((UPD and !TRG) and !UK) and REW)"),"[COL_NAME]=[EXPRESSION]", " , " , "", "UPD AND TRG AND (NOT UK)")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "W")%> AS S where ( <%=odiRef.getColList("",odiRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")+".[COL_NAME]=S.[COL_NAME]", " and ", "", "UK") %> ) and S.IND_UPDATE = 'U'

insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(odiRef.getColList(",", " ", "", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)"),"[COL_NAME]", ",
	" , "", "((INS and TRG) and REW)")%> ) select <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(odiRef.getColList(",", " ", "", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)"),"[EXPRESSION]", ",
	" , "", "((INS and TRG) and REW)")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> where IND_UPDATE = 'I'
